definitions.definition: An indigenous Muscogee people of central Alabama, or a member of said people. [from 1708]

main_definition: An indigenous Muscogee people of central Alabama, or a member of said people. [from 1708]

definitions.definition: A state of the United States . Capital: Montgomery . Largest city: Birmingham .
A river in Alabama ; flowing 318 miles from the confluence of the Tallapoosa and Coosa near Coosada until its confluence with the Tombigbee , forming the Mobile , near Calvert .
A Muskogean language, spoken by the Alabama people.
A town in New York ; named for the state.
